abstract: Not to mention the Democratic presidential race. It can be done, if you put your mind to it.
snippet: Not to mention the Democratic presidential race. It can be done, if you put your mind to it.
lead_paragraph: Gail Collins: Bret, there are only two subjects in our current political world: impeachment and the Democratic presidential race. Both are certainly … exciting.

abstract: He doesn’t want a revolution. He doesn’t have a movement. He could still win this thing.
snippet: He doesn’t want a revolution. He doesn’t have a movement. He could still win this thing.
lead_paragraph: Joe Biden has no trouble lingering in place, wherever he is, especially if there’s a point he wants to finish — or start. Generally it does not matter how many people are prodding him along or waiting out in the cold. And it seemed important to Biden that I hear what he was talking about right now before we finished.

abstract: Iowa caucusgoers aren’t just asking about the one issue that’s dominating the headlines.

lead_paragraph: MARSHALLTOWN, Iowa — With three jurors in the impeachment trial traipsing about Iowa this past weekend, you’d expect someone — anyone! — planning to attend the Iowa caucuses to ask the presidential candidates about impeachment.

headline_print_headline: A Curious Cameo In the Trump Trial

abstract: A guide to the terms and phrases we’ve heard during the Senate impeachment trial of President Trump.
snippet: A guide to the terms and phrases we’ve heard during the Senate impeachment trial of President Trump.
lead_paragraph: Many big political news events give rise to colorful terms that stick in the public memory. The Teapot Dome. The Saturday night massacre. The stained blue dress. Hanging chads.

abstract: As the liberal Bernie Sanders tightens his grip in Iowa, more traditional Democrats remain split among his four leading competitors, or are unsure altogether of whom to support.
snippet: As the liberal Bernie Sanders tightens his grip in Iowa, more traditional Democrats remain split among his four leading competitors, or are unsure altogether of whom to support.
lead_paragraph: BETTENDORF, Iowa — As they streamed out of the ballroom following a Scott County fund-raising banquet Saturday night, one after the other Iowa Democrats admitted that they still had not decided whom to support just over a week before the state’s presidential caucuses.

lead_paragraph: Welcome to our new On Politics morning newsletter, a daily political analysis of the 2020 elections, based on reporting by Times journalists and interviews with Democratic and Republican officials, voters, pollsters and strategists.

abstract: The fracking ban pushed by Senators Elizabeth Warren and Bernie Sanders  epitomizes a Democratic quandary: Appeal to swing voters or energize a liberal movement?
snippet: The fracking ban pushed by Senators Elizabeth Warren and Bernie Sanders  epitomizes a Democratic quandary: Appeal to swing voters or energize a liberal movement?
lead_paragraph: PITTSBURGH — Though they are both Democrats, John Fetterman, Pennsylvania’s lieutenant governor, and Bill Peduto, this city’s mayor, have their differences on the environment.

abstract: The current system is a form of white privilege that warps the process.
snippet: The current system is a form of white privilege that warps the process.
lead_paragraph: The Iowa caucuses and New Hampshire primary owe their first-in-the-nation status partly to circumstance. Decades ago, Iowa’s caucus was the initial step in a long, complex process that the state used to award delegates, which meant that the voting had to happen early in the year. New Hampshire was mostly trying to save money — by scheduling its primary on the same day as many annual town meetings, which were held before the spring mud season.
